review_blob: Very nice beer with aroma and flavor of nicely roasted coffee and full, slick mouthfeel thanks to the oats.  Could use just a bit more stout to it to even out the coffee.

Loved this beer!  Came in a 16.9 oz. bottle with a label that looks like one of my homebrew labels.  What it lacked in outward appearance, it more than made up for inside.  Beautiful amber color with a billowing/creamy tan head.  Aroma is American hops and sweet caramel malt.  Flavor is very much like the aroma.  Deceptively smooth and easy drinking for a 7.5%+ beer.  As in the pale, very well crafted and balanced slightly towards the hops.  Very glad to find it here in	SW Virginia!
Excellent, sessionable, well balanced beer!  Very happy to find it here in SW Virginia.

Very nice session beer.  Aroma is citrus and pine with soft malt in the background.  Pours a cloudy light orange with a nice sized white head.  Flavor is tame, with nice hop character and some mineral.  Mouthfeel is light and dry/crisp, making you want another.  Very nice APA.

Wonderful example of the style!  Enticing, heavenly hop aroma from extensive dry hopping/late kettle additions.  Flavor is equally sublime.  Alcohol and bitterness are both high, but take a back seat.  One of my favorites!
beer_name: Stone Sublimely Self Righteous Black IPA
